# Electron UI Framework Standard

- Use `React + Ant Design` as the default frontend UI framework in `ElectronApp/`.
- Prefer Ant Design components before custom implementations (`Layout`, `Menu`, `Tabs`, `Table`, `Dropdown`, `Modal`, `Form`, `Tooltip`).
- For desktop tables, prefer `Table` with built-in scroll/selection/ellipsis; only add custom drag/sort wrappers when framework behavior is insufficient.
- For right-click and submenu interactions, prefer framework menu APIs; custom overlay/timer logic requires explicit reason comments.
- Keep styling token-driven with centralized theme/CSS variables; avoid page-level hard-coded spacing/radius/colors.
- Keep window chrome behavior (title bar/minimize/maximize/close) in dedicated components and IPC utilities, not mixed into business pages.
- After migration/refactor, remove replaced UI paths and obsolete component flows immediately.

## Example

```text
BAD: ad-hoc context menu implementation duplicated across pages.
GOOD: shared menu behavior built with Ant Design Dropdown/Menu + reusable handlers.
```
